  "text": "represents the filter of length K, and parameter r represents the interval at which the dilation is used to sample the input signal. In default filtering operation, r = 1. The dilated convolution is used in convolution operations [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] , which add \"holes\" with a value of 0 between the pixels of the convolution kernel. For a convolution kernel of size k×k, the actual convolution kernel size k result = k+(k− 1)×(r −1). As shown in Fig. 1, (a) is the default convolution, and (b), (c) and (d) are the convolution kernels for kernels for r = 2, 3, and 4, respectively.",
